# Week 8 - Day 4  
## Next Greater Element (Stack)

### üìå Topics Covered
- Next Greater Element (NGE)
- Stack-based problem solving
- Monotonic Stack concept

### üß† Problem Overview
For each element in the array, find the **next greater element on the right side**.
If no such element exists, return `-1`.

### üöÄ Approach
- Use a **stack** to keep elements whose NGE is not found yet.
- Traverse the array from right to left.
- Pop elements smaller than or equal to the current element.
- The top of the stack (if exists) is the next greater element.

### üß© LeetCode Problem
- **496. Next Greater Element I**
- Link: https://leetcode.com/problems/next-greater-element-i/

### ‚è± Time & Space Complexity
- **Time:** O(n)
- **Space:** O(n)

nextgreater.cpp
  #include<iostream>
#include<vector>
#include<stack>
using namespace std;
void nextGreator(vector<int>& price,vector<int>& ans,stack<int>& s){
    for (int i = price.size()-1;i>=0;i--)
    {
         while ( s.size()>0 && s.top() <= price[i])
        {
            s.pop();
        }
        if(!s.empty() && s.top() > price[i]){
            ans[i] = s.top();
        }
        if(s.empty()) ans[i] = -1; 
             s.push(price[i]);
    }
}
int main(){
    vector<int> price = {1,4,5,42,4,5,21,3};
    vector<int> ans(price.size(),0);
    stack<int> s;
    nextGreator(price,ans,s);
    for(int x : ans){
        cout<<x<<" ";
    }

}


496.cpp
  class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> nextGreaterElement(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {
        vector<int> ans(nums1.size(),0);
        stack<int> s;
       unordered_map<int,int> m;   // key=num2[i] val = nextgreator element of num2[i]
       for(int i = nums2.size()-1;i>=0;i--){
            while(s.size() > 0 && s.top() <= nums2[i]) s.pop();

            if(!s.empty() && s.top() > nums2[i]){
                m[nums2[i]] = s.top();
            }
            if(s.empty()) m[nums2[i]] = -1;
            s.push(nums2[i]);
       }

       for(int i=0;i<nums1.size();i++){
            ans[i] = m[nums1[i]]; 
       }

    return ans;
    }
};
